fulltitle: The Sound of Ben Webster: Part One
description:
The first of a National Jazz Museum in Harlem series on the tenor saxophonist BEN WEBSTER (1909-73), hosted by the Museum's Senior Scholar, Loren Schoenberg. 
This segment covers his birth through his first tenure with Fletcher Henderson's band in 1934.
